'.\" -*- nroff -*-
.TH KAFSIMAGE 8 "2026-03-17" "kafs 0.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
kafsimage \- export offline KAFS image data in metadata-only, raw, or sparse modes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kafsimage
.B --metadata-only
.RB [ --verify ]
.I src-image
.I dst-file
.PP
.B kafsimage
.B --raw
.RB [ --verify ]
.I src-image
.I dst-file
.PP
.B kafsimage
.B --sparse
.RB [ --verify ]
.I src-image
.I dst-file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kafsimage
reads an offline source image and writes an export file in metadata-only, raw,
or sparse mode.
The source image is never modified.
With
.BR --metadata-only ,
current v0 behavior copies the metadata prefix
.IR [0, first_data_block * block_size) .
With
.BR --raw ,
the full source image is copied byte-for-byte.
With
.BR --sparse ,
all-zero chunks are written as sparse holes while preserving logical file size.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --metadata-only
Enable metadata-only export mode.
.TP
.B --raw
Enable full-image raw copy mode.
.TP
.B --sparse
Enable sparse full-image copy mode (zero chunks become holes).
.TP
.B --verify
After export, verify destination bytes match the copied range.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Export succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
I/O, bounds, or verification failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kafs (1),
.BR kafsctl (1),
.BR kafsdump (8),
.BR fsck.kafs (8),
.BR mkfs.kafs (8),
.BR kafsresize (8),
.BR kafs-info (8)
.SH AUTHOR
kafs project.
